{"version":"https://jsonfeed.org/version/1","title":"Hacker News: Newest","description":"Hacker News RSS","home_page_url":"https://news.ycombinator.com/newest","items":[{"id":"https://news.ycombinator.com/item?id=47225130","title":"The workers behind Meta's smart glasses can see everything","content_html":"\n\u003cp\u003eArticle URL: \u003ca href=\"https://www.svd.se/a/K8nrV4/metas-ai-smart-glasses-and-data-privacy-concerns-workers-say-we-see-everything\"\u003ehttps://www.svd.se/a/K8nrV4/metas-ai-smart-glasses-and-data-privacy-concerns-workers-say-we-see-everything\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eComments URL: \u003ca href=\"https://news.ycombinator.com/item?id=47225130\"\u003ehttps://news.ycombinator.com/item?id=47225130\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003ePoints: 279\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e# Comments: 151\u003c/p\u003e\n","url":"https://www.svd.se/a/K8nrV4/metas-ai-smart-glasses-and-data-privacy-concerns-workers-say-we-see-everything","external_url":"https://news.ycombinator.com/item?id=47225130","date_published":"2026-03-02T22:32:35Z","author":{"name":"sandbach","url":"https://news.ycombinator.com/user?id=sandbach"}},{"id":"https://news.ycombinator.com/item?id=47224118","title":"Welcome (back) to Macintosh","content_html":"\n\u003cp\u003eArticle URL: \u003ca href=\"https://take.surf/2026/03/01/welcome-back-to-macintosh\"\u003ehttps://take.surf/2026/03/01/welcome-back-to-macintosh\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eComments URL: \u003ca href=\"https://news.ycombinator.com/item?id=47224118\"\u003ehttps://news.ycombinator.com/item?id=47224118\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003ePoints: 182\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e# Comments: 107\u003c/p\u003e\n","url":"https://take.surf/2026/03/01/welcome-back-to-macintosh","external_url":"https://news.ycombinator.com/item?id=47224118","date_published":"2026-03-02T21:09:47Z","author":{"name":"Udo_Schmitz","url":"https://news.ycombinator.com/user?id=Udo_Schmitz"}},{"id":"https://news.ycombinator.com/item?id=47223620","title":"British Columbia to end time changes, adopt year-round daylight time","content_html":"\n\u003cp\u003eArticle URL: \u003ca href=\"https://www.cbc.ca/news/canada/british-columbia/b-c-adopting-year-round-daylight-time-9.7111657\"\u003ehttps://www.cbc.ca/news/canada/british-columbia/b-c-adopting-year-round-daylight-time-9.7111657\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eComments URL: \u003ca href=\"https://news.ycombinator.com/item?id=47223620\"\u003ehttps://news.ycombinator.com/item?id=47223620\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003ePoints: 325\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e# Comments: 186\u003c/p\u003e\n","url":"https://www.cbc.ca/news/canada/british-columbia/b-c-adopting-year-round-daylight-time-9.7111657","external_url":"https://news.ycombinator.com/item?id=47223620","date_published":"2026-03-02T20:30:52Z","author":{"name":"ireflect","url":"https://news.ycombinator.com/user?id=ireflect"}},{"id":"https://news.ycombinator.com/item?id=47222270","title":"A case for Go as the best language for AI agents","content_html":"\n\u003cp\u003eArticle URL: \u003ca href=\"https://getbruin.com/blog/go-is-the-best-language-for-agents/\"\u003ehttps://getbruin.com/blog/go-is-the-best-language-for-agents/\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eComments URL: \u003ca href=\"https://news.ycombinator.com/item?id=47222270\"\u003ehttps://news.ycombinator.com/item?id=47222270\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003ePoints: 145\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e# Comments: 216\u003c/p\u003e\n","url":"https://getbruin.com/blog/go-is-the-best-language-for-agents/","external_url":"https://news.ycombinator.com/item?id=47222270","date_published":"2026-03-02T18:48:36Z","author":{"name":"karakanb","url":"https://news.ycombinator.com/user?id=karakanb"}},{"id":"https://news.ycombinator.com/item?id=47221994","title":"Bars close and hundreds lose jobs as US firm buys Brewdog in £33M deal","content_html":"\n\u003cp\u003eArticle URL: \u003ca href=\"https://www.bbc.com/news/articles/c05v0p1d0peo\"\u003ehttps://www.bbc.com/news/articles/c05v0p1d0peo\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eComments URL: \u003ca href=\"https://news.ycombinator.com/item?id=47221994\"\u003ehttps://news.ycombinator.com/item?id=47221994\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003ePoints: 117\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e# Comments: 100\u003c/p\u003e\n","url":"https://www.bbc.com/news/articles/c05v0p1d0peo","external_url":"https://news.ycombinator.com/item?id=47221994","date_published":"2026-03-02T18:29:26Z","author":{"name":"tartoran","url":"https://news.ycombinator.com/user?id=tartoran"}},{"id":"https://news.ycombinator.com/item?id=47220809","title":"Show HN: Govbase – Follow a bill from source text to news bias to social posts","content_html":"\n\u003cp\u003eGovbase tracks every bill, executive order, and federal regulation from official sources (Congress.gov, Federal Register, White House). An AI pipeline breaks each one down into plain-language summaries and shows who it impacts by demographic group.\u003cp\u003eIt also ties each policy directly to bias-rated news coverage and politician social posts on X, Bluesky, and Truth Social. You can follow a single bill from the official text to how media frames it to what your representatives are saying about it.\u003cp\u003eFree on web, iOS, and Android.\u003cp\u003e\u003ca href=\"https://govbase.com\" rel=\"nofollow\"\u003ehttps://govbase.com\u003c/a\u003e\u003cp\u003eI'd love feedback from the community, especially on the data pipeline or what policy areas/features you feel are missing.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003chr\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eComments URL: \u003ca href=\"https://news.ycombinator.com/item?id=47220809\"\u003ehttps://news.ycombinator.com/item?id=47220809\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003ePoints: 139\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e# Comments: 63\u003c/p\u003e\n","url":"https://govbase.com","external_url":"https://news.ycombinator.com/item?id=47220809","date_published":"2026-03-02T17:08:53Z","author":{"name":"foxfoxx","url":"https://news.ycombinator.com/user?id=foxfoxx"}},{"id":"https://news.ycombinator.com/item?id=47219668","title":"Ask HN: Who is hiring? (March 2026)","content_html":"\n\u003cp\u003ePlease state the location and include REMOTE for remote work, REMOTE (US)\nor similar if the country is restricted, and ONSITE when remote work is \u003ci\u003enot\u003c/i\u003e an option.\u003cp\u003ePlease only post if you personally are part of the hiring company—no\nrecruiting firms or job boards. One post per company. If it isn't a household name,\nexplain what your company does.\u003cp\u003ePlease only post if you are actively filling a position and are committed\nto replying to applicants.\u003cp\u003eCommenters: please don't reply to job posts to complain about\nsomething. It's off topic here.\u003cp\u003eReaders: please only email if you are personally interested in the job.\u003cp\u003eSearchers: try \u003ca href=\"http://nchelluri.github.io/hnjobs/\" rel=\"nofollow\"\u003ehttp://nchelluri.github.io/hnjobs/\u003c/a\u003e,\n\u003ca href=\"https://hnjobs.emilburzo.com\" rel=\"nofollow\"\u003ehttps://hnjobs.emilburzo.com\u003c/a\u003e, or this (unofficial) Chrome extension:\n\u003ca href=\"https://chromewebstore.google.com/detail/hn-hiring-pro/mpfaljjblphnlloddaplgicpkinikjlp\" rel=\"nofollow\"\u003ehttps://chromewebstore.google.com/detail/hn-hiring-pro/mpfal...\u003c/a\u003e.\u003cp\u003eDon't miss this other fine thread: \u003ci\u003eWho wants to be hired?\u003c/i\u003e \u003ca href=\"https://news.ycombinator.com/item?id=47219667\"\u003ehttps://news.ycombinator.com/item?id=47219667\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003chr\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eComments URL: \u003ca href=\"https://news.ycombinator.com/item?id=47219668\"\u003ehttps://news.ycombinator.com/item?id=47219668\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003ePoints: 150\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e# Comments: 201\u003c/p\u003e\n","url":"https://news.ycombinator.com/item?id=47219668","external_url":"https://news.ycombinator.com/item?id=47219668","date_published":"2026-03-02T16:00:27Z","author":{"name":"whoishiring","url":"https://news.ycombinator.com/user?id=whoishiring"}},{"id":"https://news.ycombinator.com/item?id=47219558","title":"Felix \"fx\" Lindner has died","content_html":"\n\u003cp\u003eArticle URL: \u003ca href=\"https://blog.recurity-labs.com/2026-03-02/Farewell_Felix\"\u003ehttps://blog.recurity-labs.com/2026-03-02/Farewell_Felix\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eComments URL: \u003ca href=\"https://news.ycombinator.com/item?id=47219558\"\u003ehttps://news.ycombinator.com/item?id=47219558\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003ePoints: 117\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e# Comments: 30\u003c/p\u003e\n","url":"https://blog.recurity-labs.com/2026-03-02/Farewell_Felix","external_url":"https://news.ycombinator.com/item?id=47219558","date_published":"2026-03-02T15:53:23Z","author":{"name":"is_taken","url":"https://news.ycombinator.com/user?id=is_taken"}},{"id":"https://news.ycombinator.com/item?id=47218743","title":"First in-utero stem cell therapy for fetal spina bifida repair is safe: study","content_html":"\n\u003cp\u003eArticle URL: \u003ca href=\"https://health.ucdavis.edu/news/headlines/first-ever-in-utero-stem-cell-therapy-for-fetal-spina-bifida-repair-is-safe-study-finds/2026/02\"\u003ehttps://health.ucdavis.edu/news/headlines/first-ever-in-utero-stem-cell-therapy-for-fetal-spina-bifida-repair-is-safe-study-finds/2026/02\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eComments URL: \u003ca href=\"https://news.ycombinator.com/item?id=47218743\"\u003ehttps://news.ycombinator.com/item?id=47218743\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003ePoints: 236\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e# Comments: 47\u003c/p\u003e\n","url":"https://health.ucdavis.edu/news/headlines/first-ever-in-utero-stem-cell-therapy-for-fetal-spina-bifida-repair-is-safe-study-finds/2026/02","external_url":"https://news.ycombinator.com/item?id=47218743","date_published":"2026-03-02T14:54:58Z","author":{"nam